    <title>
      <narrative xml:lang="en">Feasibility Study - NATIONAL ICT BACKBONE NETWORK: FEASIBILITY STUDY, through Government of Nigeria</narrative>
    </title>
    <description type="1">
      <narrative xml:lang="en">USTDA is providing a 442,000 grant, to Seaquest InfroTel Niger S.A., to fund a feasibility study (FS) to assess the technical and financial viability of creating a fiber optic backbone network in Niger. This network would significantly reduce the current prohibitive cost of telephony and internet services, increase universal assess to ICT, and stimulate greater cross-border trade with Niger's neighbors. The Government of Niger views this telecommunications project as crucial to the overall economic development of the country and the expansion of the ICT sector as a whole.</narrative>
    </description>
